<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Adding General Ledger Accounts in CB 2.0</title>
</head>
<body>

<div>
    <h2 id='pageTop'>PDC Add GL Account Guide</h2>
    <hr/>
    <br/>
    <br/>
    <p><b>Part I. Adding General Ledger Accounts</b></p><br/>
    <ol>
        <li>Click the “nine dots” and type “general” in the search field. Next, click on “General Ledger Accounts”<br/>
        <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Click “New”<br/>
        <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Fill in the “Name” and “Reporting Code” fields, select the type in the “Type” dropdown.<br/>
        <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Next, select the data type you want to appear for the following fields: “Trial Balance 1”, “Trial Balance 2” and “Trial Balance 3”,  “Balance Sheet 1”, “Balance Sheet 2” and “Balance Sheet 3”.<br/>
        <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Click “Save” After some time, new GLA will be created<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Go to the CB 2.0 Home page, click “Other” in the “CB 2.0 GENERAL” panel, and then click “FF Integration”<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Note that accounts are not synchronized<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Click the “View Details” link under the “Action” column (to the right) of the table <br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Here you will see the new a general ledger account<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Close this window and click the “Map Analytics” button <br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"><br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Now the CB Accounts are synchronized<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"><br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Go to the Homepage and click on the “CB Accounts” link in the “List of Data Links” panel <br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Check that the newly created CB Account is in the EXPENSE section of the COA <br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
    </ol><br/>
    <p><b>Part II. Updating Sets </b></p><br/>
    <ol>
        <li>Go to the Homepage and click on the “Accounts sets” link in the “List of Data Links” panel <br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Click on the needed Account set to open it<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>Find the needed account in the list, enable its checkbox, and click “Save” <br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
        <li>All data sets are updated in this way<br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"><br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"><br/>
            <img src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
    </ol>

</div>
<br/>

<br/>
<hr/>


<button onclick="topFunction()" id="myBtn" title="Go to top">Top</button>

<script>
    let mybutton = document.getElementById("myBtn");
    window.onscroll = function () {
        scrollFunction()
    };

    function scrollFunction() {
        mybutton.style.display = document.body.scrollTop > 20 || document.documentElement.scrollTop > 20 ? "block" : "none";
    }

    function topFunction() {
        document.body.scrollTop = 0;
        document.documentElement.scrollTop = 0;
    }
</script>

<style>
    #myBtn {
        display: none;
        position: fixed;
        bottom: 20px;
        right: 30px;
        z-index: 99;
        font-size: 18px;
        border: 1px solid #b5e853;
        outline: none;
        background-color: #171717;
        color: #b5e853;
        cursor: pointer;
        padding: 15px;
        border-radius: 4px;
    }

    #myBtn:hover {
        background-color: #181818;
    }
</style>

</body>
</html>
